comments.content: Bobbie Davis described as a girl with a "pleasuing personality" and "nimble feet."
Called a "creole 'songbird'," using scare quotes, perhaps to point out her queerness.
"starring in renditions of up-to-date hit songs, is a songstress worthy of commendation."
Name inferred from Times Union, July 23, 1935, 15
